The paper proposes a new method for Collaborative Filtering using deep generative models, specifically Variational Autoencoder (VAE). This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on recommendation systems, which is a common application of Collaborative Filtering, indicating that it could also belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of Bayesian methods, which is a common topic in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of Stochastic Gradient Variational Bayes (SGVB) algorithm, which is a common optimization technique in Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.CL, and cs.SI.
